title: Part 3
content:
Part 3

THE CLOCK'S HANDS ticked forward, from 11:28 to 11:29 AM.

Class B had been divided into two ten-person groups to retrieve supplies under Ryuuen's command and a main force to hold back Class C. The guard group, led by Komiya and accompanied by the VIP Morofuji, was headed for the supplies that appeared in E9.

Normally, the E9 location would've been completely clear. It was difficult for either Class A or Class C to target and Class B thought it would be an easy acquisition.

However, just before 11:00 AM, one concern emerged regarding the retrieval of those supplies.

A lone GPS signal that had strayed from Class A, which appeared at D6 at 9:00 in the morning.

They were now in a situation where they might coincidentally run into it.

"R-Report. Looks like that lone GPS signal is still heading our way."

Showing a slight bewilderment, Morofuji relayed Kaneda's report to her classmates.

"You say he's comin' our way, but it's just one guy, right? Some scrub like that doesn't even know where we are, so there's no need to sweat it. Besides, if we spot him, we can just shoot 'im."

With nine guards and a VIP, there was no way they could lose, Komiya replied with an air of confidence.

"But... that's probably Koenji-kun, right? There's no doubt he's a dangerous guy..."

"Don't matter. This ain't a fistfight, it's a survival game, ya know? Doesn't matter who pulls the trigger, the result's the same, so there's nothin' to be on guard for. More importantly, we gotta grab the supplies and get back to the main unit, or we'll be in deep shit if Class C makes a move."

The number of students in the main unit and in Class C were evenly matched. It wasn't out of the question that Ayanokouji, seeing it as an opportunity, might suddenly go on the offensive. That was precisely why Ryuuen ordered them to return as soon as possible.

"What should we do, Oda-kun...? Is it okay to let him go?"

Oda, having been called, thought for a moment before telling her to contact Kaneda and ask for Ryuuen's instructions and then decided to follow Komiya.

Unable to hide her anxiety, Morofuji operated the radio again and again.

However—

"It's no use. He must be talking to someone else, I can't get through at all."

There was only one commander and if communications with the VIPs were congested, the line wouldn't connect.

When he was communicating with someone else, a period of radio silence was inevitable.

"See, I told ya you're worryin' too much. If we run into him, I'll put a round right through his heart. With this partner of mine that took out four guys during the ambush!"

Laughing, Komiya took the shotgun in his hands and struck a pose as if to show off.

"Where are you, Koenji!"

Shouting confidently, Komiya ran out and pointed the muzzle of his shotgun left and right.

"Here!? It's over here, huh!?"

With a Bang! Bang!, he fired the shotgun twice into the dark forest.

"Hey, don't go wasting so many shots~"

"Heh heh, what's the harm? He could actually be hiding, you know."

Looking amused, Komiya took out the magazine and reloaded it.

"That guy's getting carried away. That's totally a death flag, isn't it?"

Laughing in amusement, Yamawaki spoke to Kinoshita, who was walking beside her.

"Guys are so dumb. To think they could find fighting with these things fun."

Kinoshita sighed, staring coldly at the assault rifle in her hands.

"You say that, but when we charged Class C, you looked like you were having fun shooting. I saw you."

"Th-that was... I mean, I just got kinda caught up in the moment, you know—"

Blushing that he'd seen an unexpected side of her, Kinoshita sharply smacked Yamawaki on the shoulder.

"Agh—!?"

Immediately after, a voice cried out in agony.

"H-Huh!?"

She didn't remember hitting him that hard, Kinoshita thought, but the voice that cried out wasn't Yamawaki's. It was Komiya, who was walking at the front. He crumpled to the ground.

He simultaneously dropped the shotgun he'd been holding loosely.

For a brief moment, the students walking behind Komiya couldn't comprehend what happened.

"Hey, Komiya, what are you doin'—"

Immediately after, Kinoshita, who was right beside Yamawaki as she started to speak, also felt a sharp pain pierce her abdomen.

Splat!

Along with that sound came the sensation of an impact and liquid spreading across her abdomen.

"Ow!"

The impact itself wasn't that strong, but such a cry escaped her at the unexpected shot.

It was then that Yamawaki finally understood what was happening.

"Gah—she’s been shot! There's an enemy!!"

Triggered by Yamawaki's shout, a paintball landed on the side of Yabu, who was standing dazedly nearby and another on Sonoda's left thigh and 'out' warnings were issued from their wristwatches.

It was only then that the panicked students each raised their paint guns and with many eyes, frantically scanned left and right, focusing on the area ahead.

However, they couldn't spot the enemy that was shooting at them.

"I-It's gotta be Koenji! Koenji's close! Isn't Kaneda gonna say anything!?"

He exploded with frustration at the commander for not reporting the approaching danger.

"I haven't been able to get through at all!!"

"This makes no sense!"

They continued to shout in a panic as the guards formed a circle to protect the VIP, Morofuji.

But they couldn't find Koenji, or even a single human figure.

"Where are they shooting from!?"

"I dunno!"

A sharp sound rang out and by the time they noticed, a paintball struck someone else.

Not a single wasted shot and each one was precise.

Another shot flew from out of nowhere and Yamawaki was hit.

Predicting their opponent's position from the point of impact, the remaining four fired back.

But still, there was no one in sight.

"Why are you attacking us, Koenji!"

There was nothing strange about it, as they were enemies, but Komiya, who was now 'out,' shouted at the unseen Koenji, not having expected him to participate in the exam.

"It's just one person, isn't it? We can't lose to him!"

The girl, Nishino, exhaled and started running toward the direction the paintballs seemed to be coming from.

"Wait, Nishino!"

Oda shouted, but immediately after, Nishino was also shot and she fell forward in shock.

The Class B students were deeply shaken by the extraordinary situation of six students being eliminated in less than thirty seconds.

They fired their guns wildly, paintballs hitting and splattering on trees, the ground, leaves—everywhere.

"Where the hell are you!"

"It is Koenji, right!?"

"I don't know!"

One by one, they were taken down, until all eight guards surrounding Morofuji were 'out.'

"What's... what's happen—"

Suzuki was stunned as his allies were taken down one after another by an unseen enemy.

At that moment, just as a call from Kaneda came in over the radio for Morofuji, that very Suzuki was shot in the shoulder and his wristwatch issued an alert.

Morofuji, the VIP who was being protected, frantically tried to run away, but she tripped and fell.

"M-Morofuji! He's here, he's here! Run!"

From the direction the eliminated student had shouted toward, Koenji appeared, walking with a confident stride.

Morofuji picked up a weapon an ally had dropped and aimed it at Koenji.

"D-Don't come any closer!"

"You're the VIP, aren't you? If you were to fight back, you would simply be eliminated for nothing."

In response to Koenji's calm admonishment, Komiya stood up and ran over.

"What do you think you're doing!"

"There is nothing to it, is there? I am from Class A, you are from Class B. We're enemies."

"Th-That's...! I mean, how'd you find us when you're all alone!"

"My, my. I had no knowledge that I would stumble upon you. However, when one hears voices and gunshots so unsuited for this great wilderness, it is something one would understand whether one likes it or not. Am I wrong?"

The sound of a cocky Komiya provoking Koenji and the sound of gunfire.

That was what led him to their location, Koenji answered.

"I enjoyed the uninhabited island for a day and thinking I had my fill, was on my way back to the ship—but I thought I'd give this a try for the novelty of it. That is all."

Saying so, he raised his assault rifle and grinned.

"Damn it, this is your fault, Komiya!"

"S-Sorry..."

"Don't be so quick to blame him. Thanks to him, I've had some fun. Now that I've tried it for myself, this so-called survival game is quite entertaining, you know."

The muzzle pointed at them came from Koenji, who'd just thanked them.

Sensing she was out, Morofuji closed both eyes, but there was no sign of her being shot.

"Have you come to collect the supplies in this area, perhaps?"

"W-Well..."

"I should think it would be for your own good to answer honestly."

"...Y-Yeah. There's ammo... so we came to get it..."

"Is that so? In that case, you may take the supplies and return with them to Class B."

"What... do you mean?"

"Being defeated by me was nothing more than a series of unfortunate events. It would be a pity to single out Class B and bully them for no reason, wouldn't it?"

"Don't you dare fall for it, Morofuji! He's bound to shoot you in the back once you open the box! Koenji wants the ammo!"

"Y-Yeah!"

Morofuji nodded, taking the advice from the student who'd been eliminated.

Seeing this, Koenji let out a light sigh.

"My, my, that's quite the misjudgment. For me, winning or losing this special exam is a matter of supreme indifference. I have no interest in whether I defeat the VIP here, or whether I obtain the supplies. However, for all of you, the VIP's points are a crucial element, are they not? And the supplies as well..."

"Oh, well," Koenji muttered and began to walk away.

"A-Are you really letting me go?"

"You're quite persistent, aren't you? If you desire it so much, shall I eliminate you here and send you on your way?"

When he pointed the muzzle of the assault rifle at Morofuji, the sheer force of it made her shake her head vigorously from side to side.

"Very well. I shall take my leave now. I trust you will take care not to get in my way again. I am, after all, thinking of returning to the ship soon."

It was an act of kindness, in Koenji's own way.

And it was also a strong warning that absolutely must not be defied.
